This paper proposes a method to accelerate deep convolutional neural networks through filter pruning. The paper focuses on image classification benchmarks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces a new pruning criterion and a meta pruning framework, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves updating the network at each iteration, which suggests that it may belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves optimizing the filter distribution, which suggests that it may also belong to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
